STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. GERALD BRUCE COOLEY, Appellant. (No. 28913) 510 P2d 357 Gary D. Babcock, Public Defender, Salem, argued the cause and filed the brief for appellant. Thomas H. Denney, Assistant Attorney General, Salem, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief were Lee Johnson, Attorney General, and John W. Osburn, Solicitor General, Salem.

Argued May 25,

affirmed May 25, 1973

Before Schwab, Chief Judge, and Port and Thorn- . ton, Judges.
